Understand How to Run Jasmine Tests

Documentation: [https://developer.c3.ai/docs/7.19.1/topic/testing-jasmine-testing-framework](https://developer.c3.ai/docs/7.19.1/topic/testing-jasmine-testing-framework)

1.  How do I run Jasmine tests?

-   Navigate to Tools -> Tester in your C3 AI Static Console
-   Locate the Jasmine test you want to run in your file system and drag/drop or open the test(s) from your filesystem.
-   Click the play button to run the test

1.  How do I debug Jasmine tests?

-   In the test you are writing, use the insert a line with the following to pause the test:

-   debugger;

-   Run the test using the Console UI and open Chrome's developer tools.
-   The test should pause at the debugger statement like the following:

3.  How do I run tests using TestRunner? (This should mimic running the test from Jenkins; future automated testing process)

-   Make sure to provision the application using the –E flag

-   c3 prov tag -t <tenant>:<tag> -u BA -p BA -c panda -E

-   Run the following (inserting your tenant, tag, and test name):

-   c3 tester -t <tenant>:<tag> --test-runner-type JasmineTestRunner --test-path "/test_WorkUnitCode.js" -u BA:BA -c panda
